    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "Let's be careful about who's doing what here. IPython isn't stripping any strings, it's not involved at all.\r\n\r\nThe two components are\r\n\r\n1. the HTML generated by `DataFrame._repr_html_`\r\n2. the rendering of that HTML in the notebook\r\n\r\nI don't think we're interested in messing with the CSS. That's best left to others (with the defaults set by the notebook). The bits that we have only deal with alignment of MultiIndexes, which are somewhat unique to pandas.\r\n\r\nOn item 1, it *does* looks like we `strip` strings somewhere, removing leading and trailing spaces, in `to_html` if you want to take a look at that."
  },
