    "body": "Displaying HTML would effectively strip the spaces anyway. Try making a .html file with this in:\r\n\r\n```html\r\n<table style=\"border: 1px solid black;\">\r\n<tr><td>    a   bc  </td></tr>\r\n</table>\r\n```\r\n\r\nYou'll only see a box containing `a bc` - all the other spaces are collapsed.\r\n\r\nTo avoid this, pandas would have to replace spaces with non-breaking spaces `&nbsp;`. They aren't collapsed. That could cause problems for displaying longer strings, though, because it breaks wrapping."
